Testing

1. Add testing libraries to project's Gemfile
  * teaspoon  (testing framework)
  * phantomjs (headless web client)
    --> Note: we link to the github repo of the phantomjs gem so
              we have the option of using capybara 2.1+
              https://github.com/modeset/teaspoon/issues/102#issuecomment-23727629
  * tapout    (test harness)

2. Install Istanbul with npm (code coverage)
  * npm install -g istanbul

3.
